OCS INVENTORY INSTALLATION 

STEP 1 : Prerequisites 
1.1 update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

1.2 Make sure LAMP stack (apache, MYSQL/mariaDB,PHP)installed

sudo systemctl status apache2 
sudo systemctl status mariadb
php-v   

STEP 2 Install packages required by OCS inventory server 
2.1 install make,gcc,git& curl on the system
sudo apt install git curl wget make cmake gcc make 

2.2 install php extensions required by OCS inventory server
sudo apt -y install php -mbstring php -xml php -mysql php -zip php -pclzip php -gd php -soap php -curl php -json libapache2 -mod -perl2 libapache2 -dbi -perl libapache -db -perl libapache2 -mod -php libarchive -zip -perl mariadb -clienr

STEP 3 install and enable perl modules required by OCS server 
3.1 install perl modules
sudo apt -y install perl libxml-simple-perl libcompress-zlib-perl libdbi-perl libdbd-mysql-perl libnet-ip-perl libsoap-lite-perl libio-compress-perl libapache-dbi-perl  libapache2-mod-perl2 libapache2-mod-perl2-dev

3.2 enable perl modules
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install Apache2::SOAP'
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install XML::Entities'
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install Net::IP'
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install Apache::DBI'
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install Mojolicious'
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install Switch'
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install Plack::Handler'
STEP 4 create database for OCS inventory Server 
sudo mysql -uroot -p
CREATE DATABASE ocs;
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON ocs.* TO ocs_user IDENTIFIED BY "strongpassword";
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT

STEP 5 Download OCS inventroy latest version from official website 
5.1 Access officail website and get link to download
wget (paste link)
  
STEP 6 install OCS inventory server 
edit setup.sh script 
sudo vim setup.sh 

6.2 run setup.sh script to install ocs inventory server

STEP 7 configure OCS inventory Server 
7..1 enable apache configure for OCS inventory Server

sudoln-s/etc/apache2/conf-available/ocsinventory-reports.conf/etc/apache2/conf-enabled/ocsinventory-reports.conf
sudo ln -s /etc/apache2/conf-available/z-ocsinventory-server.conf /etc/apache2/conf-enabled/z-ocsinventory-server.conf
sudo ln -s /etc/apache2/conf-available/zz-ocsinventory-restapi.conf /etc/apache2/conf-enabled/zz-ocsinventory-restapi.conf

7.2 change the ownership of the ocsinventory-reports directory to www-data 
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/lib/ocsinventory-reports
RESTART THE APCHE2 SERVER
sudo systemctl restart apache2 
 

Check ip on the server 
on the web interface 
ipadress/ocsreports/install.php 
 
input database 

for security need remote install.php file 
sudo mv install.php install.php.bak







